Here is the review of the `km-explorer` project, focusing on race conditions in session restore and lifecycle ownership bugs.

### Part 1: Race Conditions in Session Restore and Scroll Position Handling

The session restore logic in `AppState` (`packages/app/src/lib/state/index.svelte.ts`) attempts to restore a complex navigation stack (List → Channel → Favorites) with specific scroll targets. The following race conditions exist:

#### 1. The "Ghost Scroll" Race (ListView Restoration)
**Location:** `AppState.restoreForegroundList` (Lines ~230-245)
**Issue:** The code calls `paginateToTarget` to find the video, then immediately calls `scrollToTarget`.
```typescript
// packages/app/src/lib/state/index.svelte.ts
const found = await this.searchState.paginateToTarget(entry.scrollTarget, token.signal);
// ...
if (found && !restoreSignal.aborted) {
    await this.waitForLayout(); // Waits for DOM height > clientHeight
    // ...
    const scrolled = this.scrollToTarget(entry.scrollTarget);
```
